  "text": "The mean mass size distribution of sodium is reported in Fig. 12 showing that, whatever the season, 80 % of the sodium mass is present on particles whose diameter ranges between 0.3 and 2.6 µm, the distribution peaking between 1 and 1.6 µm diameter. These observations are consistent with those from [CITATION_1] showing a maximum between 1.1 and 2.1 µm diameter. However, the finding of a larger size mode in summer (around 1-2 µm diameter) than in winter (submicrometric mode) is not confirmed here by our data.",
